---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Captcha from "../components/Captcha.svelte";
import Svg from "../components/Svg.svelte";
import ProgressWatcher from "../components/ProgressWatcher.svelte";
import ProgressCard from "../components/ProgressCard.svelte";
import dotsBig from "../assets/img/dots-big.png";
---

<Layout>
  <Captcha client:load />

  <section
    class="relative p-2.5 lg:p-5 min-h-[calc(50svh-var(--header-height)-20px)] lg:min-h-[calc(100svh-var(--header-height)-20px)] bg-yellow"
  >
    <Image
      priority
      class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0"
      src={dotsBig}
      alt=""
    />
    <div
      class="absolute max-lg:w-1/2 right-2.5 lg:right-5 bottom-2.5 lg:bottom-5"
    >
      <Svg client:load src="/svg/code.svg" class="w-full h-full" />
    </div>
    <div class="relative">
      <p class="mb-2.5 lg:mb-5">II - The Code</p>
      <h1 class="font-workbench uppercase text-7xl lg:text-9xl">
        Our Manifesto
        <br class="max-lg:hidden" />
        in the AI Era
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
        <p>
          We’re lucky – we already have a blueprint for a better future. For
          twenty years, the Mozilla Manifesto has guided what we build and how
          —and proven that empowering tech for the public good can succeed in
          the marketplace. As we grew Firefox, our Manifesto principles weren't
          just ideals, they became the foundation of a commercially viable
          alternative to monopoly control.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today we still embrace our full manifesto. But five principles from
          the manifesto are especially relevant in the age of AI:
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-10 lg:space-y-20">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5 items-center">
          <Svg client:load src="/svg/code-icon-1.svg" class="w-full" />
          <p class="col-span-2">
            HUMAN AGENCY<br /><br />in a world of AI and agents, it is more
            important than ever that technology is designed in ways that let
            people shape their own experiences online — and optimize for privacy
            where it matters to them most.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
          <Svg client:load src="/svg/code-icon-2.svg" class="w-full" />
          <p class="col-span-2">
            DECENTRALIZATION AND OPEN SOURCE<br /><br />an open, accessible
            internet depends on innovation and decentralized participation in
            the creation and use of technology. The success of open source AI
            built around transparent community practices is critical to making
            this possible in the AI era.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
          <Svg client:load src="/svg/code-icon-3.svg" class="w-full" />
          <p class="col-span-2">
            BALANCING COMMERCIAL AND PUBLIC BENEFIT<br /><br />more than ever,
            the direction of the internet and AI is defined by commercial
            players. We also need a strong cadre of public benefit players to
            create balance in the overall ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-2.5 lg:space-y-5">
        <p>
          We think about these principles every single day as we build products,
          invest in startups and organize communities with the goal of doing for
          AI what we did for the web.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="p-2.5 lg:p-5">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2.5 lg:gap-5">
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:col-start-2 space-y-5">
        <div
          class="relative overflow-hidden p-2.5 lg:p-5 outline outline-dashed bg-yellow space-y-2.5"
        >
          <h3 class="text-3xl lg:text-7xl uppercase text-center">
            <span class="font-star">THE MOZILLA</span>
            <span class="font-star">MANIFESTO:</span>
            <span class="font-star">A BLUEPRINT FOR</span>
            <span class="font-star">THE AI ERA</span>
          </h3>
          <div class="-mt-5 lg:-mt-10 -mx-5 mb-0">
            <Svg client:load src="/svg/intro1.svg" />
          </div>
          <hr class="border-dashed mt-0" />
          <h3 class="text-3xl lg:text-7xl uppercase">
            <span class="font-star">HUMAN AGENCY</span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            In a world of AI and agents, it is more important than ever that
            technology is designed in ways that let people shape their own
            experiences online — and optimize for privacy where it matters to
            them most.
          </p>
          <hr class="border-dashed mt-5" />
          <h3 class="text-3xl lg:text-7xl uppercase">
            <span class="font-star">DECENTRALIZATION</span>
            <span class="font-star">AND OPENSOURCE</span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            An open, accessible internet depends on innovation and decentralized
            participation in the creation and use of technology. The success of
            open source AI built around transparent community practices is
            critical to making this possible in the AI era.
          </p>
          <hr class="border-dashed mt-5" />
          <h3 class="text-3xl lg:text-7xl uppercase">
            <span class="font-star">BALANCING COMMERCIAL</span>
            <span class="font-star">AND PUBLIC BENEFIT</span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            More than ever, the direction of the internet and AI is defined by
            commercial players. We also need a strong cadre of public benefit
            players to create balance in the overall ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          target="_blank"
          href="/pdf/251020_Mozilla_A4_download-lq.pdf"
          class="btn invert inline-flex! items-center space-x-1.5 w-full"
        >
          <svg
            class="size-3"
            viewBox="0 0 313 313"
            fill="currentColor"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <path
              d="M0 196.49V312.86H312.97V196.74H273.64V273.46H37.88V196.49H0Z"
            ></path>
            <path
              d="M156.31 235.02C129.85 195.33 104.77 157.72 77.75 117.22H116.77V0H194.86V116.91H234.95C207.86 157.58 182.97 194.97 156.31 235.02Z"
            ></path>
          </svg>
          <span>Download manifesto</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ProgressWatcher
    client:load
    current="code"
    number="two"
    position="second"
    next="ledger"
    text="> These are the rules we live by.<br />> But words mean nothing without action."
  />

  <ProgressCard client:load full={false} />
</Layout>
